com.azure.data.cosmos.internal

Interface ISessionToken

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    VectorSessionToken

    public interface ISessionToken
    Models session token. We make assumption that instances of this interface are immutable (read only after they are constructed), so if you want to change this behaviour please review all of its uses and make sure that mutability doesn't break anything.

    • Method Detail

      • isValid

        boolean isValid(ISessionToken other)
         throws CosmosClientException
        Returns true if this instance of session token is valid with respect to other session token. This is used to decide if the client can accept server's response (based on comparison between client's and server's session token)
        Parameters:
        other - SESSION token to validate
        Returns:
        true if this instance of session token is valid with respect to other session token; false otherwise
        Throws:
        CosmosClientException

      • merge

        ISessionToken merge(ISessionToken other)
             throws CosmosClientException
        Returns a new instance of session token obtained by merging this session token with the given session token other. Merge is commutative operation, so a.Merge(b).Equals(b.Merge(a))
        Parameters:
        other - Other session token to merge
        Returns:
        Instance of merged session token
        Throws:
        CosmosClientException
